{"questionId":"35033340","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the volume, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>, of the skip is given by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>24</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>all correct intermediate working leading to given answer<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em>&nbsp;line must be seen for the final&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em> to be awarded.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35033340","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ2.5b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that the volume, V m3, of the skip is given by 24 sin θ 5+cos θ.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, midpoints","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}